# Software Engineering Book Rules

On-demand guidance from [agent-rules-books](https://github.com/ciembor/agent-rules-books). Invoke the matching skill or read its `rules.md`:

| Task | Skill |
|------|-------|
| Refactoring / cleanup | @refactoring or @refactoring-guru |
| Code review / readability | @clean-code |
| Architecture / boundaries | @clean-architecture or @a-philosophy-of-software-design |
| Domain modeling | @domain-driven-design-distilled (light) or @domain-driven-design |
| Data / consistency / events | @designing-data-intensive-applications |
| Production reliability | @release-it |
| Legacy / untested code | @working-effectively-with-legacy-code |
| General engineering | @the-pragmatic-programmer |

**One primary book per task.** Check [COMPATIBILITY.md](../agent-rules-books/COMPATIBILITY.md) before combining. For NixOS flake edits, @edit-nixos wins over book rules.
